Value.Data: Best Western Princess Hotel enjoys a central location, with car parking, shops, cultural facilities and restaurants close at hand. It is situated in a quiet neighbourhood, a stone's throw from the beautiful 'Industrilandskapet' (Industrial Landscape).

The hotel has recently been extensively refurbished, giving a modern yet very homely feel. The lobby offers the opportunity for guests to meet and enjoy the café-bar atmosphere. It serves food and drink, and free coffee and biscuits are available at all times. An extensive breakfast buffet is included in all room rates. The hotel has 117 spacious rooms, all equipped with free wireless Internet and flat-screen TV with free TV1000 movie channels, Viasat Sport, BBC, Swedish channels 1 to 6 and radio. Guests have free use of the sauna, fitness centre and lobby computers. Single and double rooms are available, and extra beds can be added in some rooms to accommodate up to five people. Reception is staffed 24 hours, enabling us to offer guests food, drink and service all round the clock. In addition to accommodation and breakfast, Best Western Princess Hotel offers a number of advantageous accommodation packages, such as the Kolmården Package, the Golf Package (with pre-booked start times), the Entertainment Package and the Concert Package. The hotel is non-smoking and bears the Nordic Ecolabel Svanen.

Latitude: 58.586659 58° 35' 11.97" Longitude: 16.185844 16° 11' 9.04" By foot Leaving the railway station through the exit at the front, walk straight ahead along Drottninggatan. Continue for about 10 minutes until you see Filmstaden cinema on the right, go through to the back and cross Gamla Rådstugugatan. Go straight ahead down Skomakaregatan and you will see the hotel on your left, at No 8. By tram At the railway station take tram line 3 towards Klockaretorpet and get out at Söder Tull. Walk down towards Nordea bank, turn left, and then turn right into Gamla Rådstugugatan. Turn left down Skomakaregatan, and you will see the hotel on your left. By car E4 northbound: take the first motorway exit towards Norrköping city. At the first roundabout, head towards Centrum, second exit on the right, continue straight ahead for a couple of kilometres, turn left into Hörngatan, continue along Gamla Rådstugugatan, and turn left into Skomakaregatan. We are opposite Filmstaden cinema and McDonald's. E4 southbound: take the first exit towards Norrköping city. At the first roundabout, head towards Centrum and follow the signs to Resecentrum/tågstationen (train station). Turn right at the station (white building) into Drottninggatan, which is also a tram route. Immediately after the bridge over the river, turn right into Gamla Rådstugugatan. Continue straight ahead for a few kilometres, then turn right into Skomakaregatan. We are opposite Filmstaden cinema and McDonald's. E22 northbound (via Söderköping): turn left at the first set of traffic lights at the junction of Södra Promenaden and Östra Promenaden, with Medley Centralbadet sports centre on your left. Go down Södra Promenaden until the second set of traffic lights, where the tram goes past. Turn right into Hörngatan, which becomes Gamla Rådstugugatan one block later. Turn left into Skomakaregatan; we are opposite Filmstaden cinema and McDonald's.
